					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">E'ci: PC Quests for Newbies</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=322752" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abm.asp?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
I started this just for fun. I went back to my home town in Kelethin and made up some "mini events" for newbies. Example, I went into wolf form, and would find a few newbies in the woods and tell of the story how an EVIL troll placed a curse on me, in which it changed me into a wolf. The only way to remove the curse was to find him in Crushbone and Remove the curse. Actually, I just met up with a troll and told him to act like he placed a curse on me. Once the newbie found him, and talked him into removing the "curse" I cancel wolf form. They come back, I thank them, and reward them with some Equip. Sometimes Banded armor, sometime magic.  Works best as ENC since you have SO many illusions. My point is, if you guys ever want to do something fun, or help some newbies.... maybe we could all get together sometime and make some mini-events like this happen. The newbies LOVE it. Adds a new spark in just killing bats.<P>

Hey you newbies, I might come back and do more, so keep an eye out for me!
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
