			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Alright, I just want to say that this is a great thing to do.  I am tired of just lvling so i can get more loot, so I can get better stuff, so i can kill more stuff, so i can lvl more, and so on.  You have to add some fun to the game or it really isn't a game anymore.  One time, when i was little, I found someone who was shouting that the first person that found him would get an item.  I got a shiny brass shield, a ketcho kori mas, and some banded, which was great for a newbie warrior.  For his kindness, i took my alter ego, a lvl 42 drood and promised him free ports whenever i was on that character. <BR>
the moral is that sometimes, being nice to newbies pays off.<BR>
<BR>
just my 2cp
