			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Some of my best moments (yeah I love to hear that ding sound but ...) have been after a frustrating day of hunting to go home to Felwithe, meet up with a young player and hand them what to them is a wonderful item.<BR>
<BR>
Twice, I happened to give something away to someone who was a child (literally) whose mom or dad had a high lvl character (uber lvl's 56 and up) yet was making their son/daughter go out and explore on their own instead of twinking them out.<BR>
<BR>
Both times, the parent described how the child's eyes lit up at their new 'toy'<BR>
<BR>
On the other hand, I HAVE had some really bad times where I'd offer an item ... no responses ... and I will say this ... don't eyeball me at the bank and beg pp or items from me just because I look like I'm rich ... you won't get a cp off me!<BR>
<BR>
At least I'm not as nasty as one guy I heard of, who in response to a beggar I know and despise, offered 2 kpp then canceled the trade!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
