	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I knew I wasnt the first one to come up with this idea and I guess I am not the first one to mention it but I had thought about doing this as well and recently (over New Years Weekend) did it on Morell Thule.<BR>
<BR>
I had been helping a new player (a HS Senior) who was playing a Paladin in the Freeport area a little here and there and having only recieved the game on Dec. 25th, was awful impatient about leveling and LOOKING like a Paly.  Well he played hard over the weekend and REALLY wanted a good 2 Handed Sword.  I told him that upon attaining the 7th Circle he was to see me.  He did so.  We met at the end of the trail in EC near West FP.<BR>
<BR>
It had gotten dark and I had sent my sweetie into West Commons to the Toll Booth with a silver ring that has no real value or stats, but is priceless to her.  I spoke to this young Paladin of wanting the ring from her and that she would not readily give it up as it was very precious to her.  I told him that he was going to have to convince her that 1)I had sent for it and 2)that he could be trusted with it.  I spoke of the dangers of a land he had never traveled - of Griffins, Giants and Werewolves not to mention 2 of the meanest Dark Elves in the land (Dragoon Zytl and hsi evil cousin).  Because it was dark, he was REALLY nervous.  He asked me if he was going to die and I told him that was all up to his skills.  With trepidation he took off on part 1.  I shadowed him from a distance.  My love made it difficult, but not impossible to get the ring and eventually he returned - proudly bearing the items I requested.  I told him he had proven himself a noble and trustworthy person and had passed the Test of Faith and Trust.<BR>
<BR>
The final part of his quest was prove his worthiness and skills in the test of bravery.  I sent him off to obtain about 10 different things from various MOBS telling him that he would get a bonus if he could return to me a Puma Skin.  About 30 minutes later he returned with all the items.  I went through an official Ceremony where he recieved his first Magic Weapon, a Velium 2 Handed Sword and for the Puma Skin he recieved and extra 10pp.<BR>
<BR>
He was thrilled with it.  He recieved no direct experience for the quest and no faction of any sort, but it was nice to hear him say &quot;Dude, you make this game SO much fun.&quot;  That is what it is all about is it not?<BR>
<BR>
I am a firm believer that players should not have things that unbalance the game. I dont like twinking for this reason, so the help I give is appropriate to the levels.  I myself am only on my first character and have been 21 for about 6 weeks.  I am having a blast.  Doing simple quests like this make the game fun for those just starting as well as those of us handing the quests out.  And it gives them a sense of EARNING what they got rather than just having someone give it to them.<BR>
<BR>
My 2c,<BR>
<BR>
Kharlkuhlinayn<BR>
Steel Warrior of the 21st Season<BR>
Morell Thule<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
